.DT
soul
Discworld player help
soul

.SH Name
.SI 5
soul - The wonderful feelings thing.
.EI

.SH Pinkfish's soul.

.SH How to use (What can it do for you?):
.SP 5 5
The feeling or atmosphere commands that you use, like smile and so
on come from your soul.  The soul used on this mud is different to most
others you will have come across.  Below are a few examples of what you
can do with this soul.
.EP

.SI 5
> smile happily at furball
You smile happily at furball.
> smile w at furball
You smile wryly at furball
> shake hands with furball
You shake hands with furball
> shake hands furball
You shake hands with furball.
.EI

.SP 5 5
The above are a few examples of what can be done with the soul.  The usage
of the command (i.e. whether you use and at or a with or whatever... well,
just use what seems right... It should work)  To see what soul commands are
available to you at any given time type
.EP

.SI 5
> look soul
Here are the commands in this hoopy soul.
smile       cry        poke
<complete list of souls omitted in this helpfile>
.EI

.SP 5 5
Any of the soul commands displayed in the long list have help available
for them.  This help shows you all the valid methods of using the soul
command and all the valid adverbs to the commands.  To find the ways you can use a soul, try 'syntax <soul command>' or 'help <soul command>'.
.EP

.SP 5 5
The first one of the options is the default.  You can select the others by
doing things like
.EP

.SI 5
> shake l
You shake your leg.
> waggle eyebrows pinkfish
You waggle your eyebrows at Ms Pinkfish.
.EI

.SP 5 5
Womble on.
.EP

.SH Colours
.SP 5 5
You can turn on and off the display of colours in souls directed at you
using the command 'options output usercolour'.  This allows you to
choose if you wish to receive coloured souls or not.  You can also set the
colour of the souls you receive using 'options colour soul'.
.EP

.SH Examples
.SI 5
> options colour soul = yellow
Set option colour soul to [%^YELLOW%^yellow%^RESET%^].

> options output usercolour = on
Set option output usercolour to on.
.EI

.SH Idea reporting souls
.SP 5 5
If you find a missing command use the following command to get it added by
someone who can.
.EP

.SH Syntax
.SP 5 5
idea soul <soul command>
.EP

.SH See also
.SI 5
alias, help, history.
.EI
